Archbishop Desmond Tutu has cast his special vote. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Archbishop Emeritus Desmond Tutu and his wife Leah have cast their special votes. Independent Electoral Committee officials met up with the couple in their Milnerton home in Cape Town on Monday morning. READ: Forest Whitaker more scared of playing Desmond Tutu than Idi Amin Tutu thanked officials after his special vote as he walked them out and waved to the media. More than 770,000 voters have registered for special votes and although polls open nationally on Wednesday. Those who applied for special votes will vote on Monday and Tuesday. Archbishop Emeritus Desmond Tutu's wife, Leah casts her special vote at their home in Milnerton, Cape Town.